Campaign Objective:
Drive in-restaurant traffic via awareness of Red Robin's $6.99 Tavern Double Burger and bottomless fries value message.
IMPORTANT_ANNOUNCEMENT__c: Salesforce Changes: New Product Updates. For those who missed the training, please watch the video recording today.
Name: Vitro Agency_Red Robin_Tavern Burger Winter Campaign_1/19/15-2/15/15
RFP_Special_Client_Requests__c: Avails;Data Segments;Deck;Representative Sitelist;Screen Shots;See Special Notes
Special_Notes_or_Campaign_Instructions__:
Campaign: Tavern: Winter 2015
Objective: Drive in-restaurant traffic via awareness of Red Robin's $6.99 Tavern Double Burger and bottomless fries value message
Primary Target: Female HH Decision Maker (W25-49) with Kids
Secondary Target: Burger Enthusiasts
Other Target Considerations: Value Seekers, Weekend Shoppers, Current Red Robin/Casual Restaurant Diners, Fun-Seeking Families and Adults, Socially-Connected Entertainment Seekers
Timing: 1/12/2015 – 2/15/2015 (5 Weeks)
Budget: $25,000
Units: Standard Display, High Impact/Unique Opportunities (see attached RFP for specific sizes/dimensions). Please do not propose any new unit sizes we did not run with you in our previous Tavern campaign, or those listed in the RFP!
Success Metrics: Intent to Visit (see attached RFP)
RFP Due: 12/4 (Thursday) or Earlier
 
This campaign is all about driving in-store traffic to Red Robin restaurants, and our strategy is to utilize everything from location-based mobile targeting, to lifestyle daily habitual activities, to content around in-season events (i.e., Superbowl XLIX, Grammy Awards, Valentine’s Day, etc.). Please thoroughly read the RFP to get a better idea of the ways we're looking to incorporate these tactics.
 
Please fill out both the "Buy Proposal Template" and "Vendor & Audience Information" tabs in the attached RFP, as well as the attached Rationale/Spec Template deck. Everyday Value: Unlike our competitors, Red Robin doesn't need to do discount offers (i.e. 2 for 2, Buy 1 Take 1 Home, etc.) because we always offer a great meal at a great price.

- Socially-connected entertainment seekers"

This year we are approaching our planning process a little differently.  We are planning Q1 separately from Q2-Q4.  Overall, we aren’t trying to reinvent the wheel with the overall strategy – we want to continue our top strategies from Q4 into Q1 (where applicable).
 
Desktop ACQ:
The KPI for Q1 has changed to cost-per-purchase.  The goal cost per purch is $1,500 and is calculated at spend / 50% of new purchases.  We will no longer be looking at carts and store locators. 
 
Since this is a continuation of Q4 top strategies, I am only asking for a scalable plan back for $300K. 
 
When you provide ACQ rates, please provide a media rate inclusive of Flashtalking ad serving fees and a non FT rate.  We are working w/ FT to bring down the non working fees on each partner, but we still need you to provide the rates in the meantime.
 
Mobile ACQ:
Mobile KPI will remain consistent – the Q1 CPSL is $20.   Please provide a scalable plan back at $65K.
 
While the mobile budget is separate from the Desktop budget, please call out how you would connect the two plans through your technology.
 
Please return the RFPs by noon Monday, Oct 20th.

Name: PGR Media_Celebrity Canada National_Q1 2015
Special_Notes_or_Campaign_Instructions__:
Primary Audience: 
Celebrity Cruises wants the affluent vacationer. In broad, he/she is 35+, with a HHI of $100K+, is willing to pay more for luxury vacations and wants pleasurable food experiences and intellectual stimulation in a vacation. It has been found that women tend to be the primary vacation planner, so the target tends to skew slightly female. 
Two subdivisions of the affluent vacationer help Celebrity more acutely target their desired consumers - the Globetrotting culture seekers and the Metropolitan trendsetters 
Globetrotting Culture Seekers: 
•	Demographically, GC’s span all age groups, are married and tend to be well-educated professionals. They consider themselves intellectual and sophisticated, not shy or traditional. They enjoy technology, staying current on business and political news, and are influential among their peers 
•	GC’s tend to be experienced travelers who seek out new experiences and destinations; they usually prefer longer trip itineraries. Within their planning, GC’s seek out fine food , wine and cultural enrichment; they also want to feel indulged, sophisticated, and are the most likely to desire romantic getaways 

Metropolitan Trendsetters: 
•	Demographically, MT’s are distinct in being very affluent, skew younger and a high male proportion. They consider themselves confident, positive and energetic. They enjoy outdoor activities, nightlife and pursue their passions. They desire meaningful, enriching and hip experiences and are willing to spend heavily for a great vacation experience 
•	MT’s are heavy users and early adopters, both of technology and entertainment; when vacationing, they seek pampering, new experiences and being part of something special. They prefer shorter itineraries

Also, please highlight Canadian reach as well as CAD specific websites in the site list
